'''Permanent vegetative cover''' refers to trees, perennial [[bunchgrass]]es and [[grassland]]s, [[legume]]s, and shrubs with an expected life span of at least 5 years.
In the United States, permanent cover is required on [[cropland]] entered into the [[Conservation Reserve Program]].
